text: Cass County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Dakota. As of the 2020 census, the population was 184,525. Cass County is the most populous county in North Dakota, accounting for nearly 24% of the state's population in 2020. Its county seat is Fargo. It is the most populous city in the state. The county was organized on October 27, 1873. ==References== Category:North Dakota counties
